HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 398
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Preston Michael
Caperton, 2025 Top Ten Senior of Collinwood
High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Preston Michael Caperton is one such exceptional student, who was
recently named a Top Ten Senior of the 2025 graduating class at Collinwood High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Caperton has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Preston Caperton has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, Preston Caperton's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely
bodes well for his future success at Columbia State Community College, where he will study
radiology technology; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Caperton's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
his parents, Cindy and Chris Caperton, his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Preston Caperton's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the
respect, admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now,
therefore,
